name: 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-3550
Reason: 16-methyl-17-oxoandrost-5-en-3-yl acetate has a melting point influenced by its functional groups relative to the base melting point of benzene, which is around 5°C. The methyl group introduces a rigid structure, which can participate in dipole interactions and raise the melting point by approximately +10°C. The oxo group introduces additional rigidity, contributing approximately +5°C. The androstane ring introduces additional rigidity, contributing approximately +20°C. The acetate group introduces a carbonyl functional group, which can participate in dipole interactions and raise the melting point by approximately +30°C. The methyl group also introduces a bulky structure, which can sterically hinder the androstane ring and lower its melting point by approximately -10°C.
